<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hangman" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hangman,</orth> a public executioner, one whose office it is to put to death in any manner: <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 2, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 2, 18</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.28" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.125" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 125</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.468" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 468</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.468" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 468</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.76" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.76" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 76</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.166" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 166</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.1.70" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.1.70" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 70</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.5.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 5, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.103" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 2.2.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. II, 2, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 2, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.1.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 1, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.179" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 4, 179</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.137" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 6, 137</bibl>. Cupid called so in jest as the executioner of human hearts: <cit><quote>the little h. dare not shoot at him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 2, 11</bibl></cit>.* <cit><quote>the h. boys,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 4, 60</bibl></cit>, probably the servants of the public executioner, not == the rascally boys, as Intpp. would have it.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>